quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  12,79,"Joseph responded, “God forbid that we should take other than the one with whom we found our property. Otherwise, we would surely be unjust.”"
  12,80,"When they lost all hope in him, they spoke privately. The eldest of them said, “Do you not know that your father had taken a solemn oath by God from you, nor how you failed him regarding Joseph before? So I am not leaving this land until my father allows me to, or God decides for me. For He is the Best of Judges"
  12,81,"Return to your father and say, ‘O our father! Your son committed theft. We testify only to what we know. We could not guard against the unforeseen"
  12,82,Ask ˹the people of˺ the land where we were and the caravan we travelled with. We are certainly telling the truth.’”
  12,83,"He cried, “No! Your souls must have tempted you to do something ˹evil˺. So ˹I am left with nothing but˺ beautiful patience! I trust God will return them all to me. Surely He ˹alone˺ is the All-Knowing, All-Wise.”"
  12,84,"He turned away from them, lamenting, “Alas, poor Joseph!” And his eyes turned white out of the grief he suppressed"
  12,85,"They said, “By God! You will not cease to remember Joseph until you lose your health or ˹even˺ your life.”"
  12,86,"He replied, “I complain of my anguish and sorrow only to God, and I know from God what you do not know"